# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NØNOS Kernel — .gitignore
# Purpose: keep the repo clean of build outputs, images, and local tooling junk
# Notes:
#   • This project is a freestanding Rust kernel (#![no_std]) built with nightly.
#   • Bootable disk images are produced via bootloader 0.11 (not cargo-bootimage).
#   • Keep Cargo.lock committed for reproducible builds of binaries.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Rust / Cargo build artifacts (workspace-safe) ────────────────────────────
/target/
**/target/
# Rationale: all compiled outputs live under target/ (debug/release by triple).
# Do NOT ignore Cargo.lock; it should remain tracked for deterministic builds.

# ── Boot images (bootloader 0.11 generates BIOS/UEFI .img files) ────────────
# Example paths:
#   target/<triple>/debug/boot-bios-<image_crate>.img
#   target/<triple>/debug/boot-uefi-<image_crate>.img
*.img
*.iso
# Tip: publish images via releases or artifacts, not in the repo.

# ── Legacy / staging directories (old ESP flows, scratch space) ─────────────
build/
build/**

# ── Logs & traces ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
qemu.log
trace.json

# ── Editor / OS cruft ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
.vs/
*.iml

# Vim / Emacs backups & swap
*~
*.swp
*.swo
.#*

# ── Debug / profiling artifacts ─────────────────────────────────────────────
*.dSYM/
*.profraw
*.profdata
*.sarif

# ── Crash dumps ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
core
core.*
